Territory of Washington COunty of Spokane}ss Territory of Washington plaintiff vs. Wilson D. Coyle Defendant} In the district Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial DIstrict thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, in said Territory.
To the sheriff of Spokane County, Greeting: In the Name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon Wm. Straub, John Caraft E. Wilson A.A. Bulb John McGovan D.R. Fauch. D. Boys John Carpenter tp be and appear before the District Court aforesaid at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the thirtieth day of April A.D. 1885 at o'clock M. to there fice evidence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Plaintiff.
Witness the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed, this 29 day of Apr A.D. 1885 Kate W. Feauerbach Clerk By R. Strobach Deputy
